# UI/UX HUD Standards

## The Two States

- **Pre-Flight** (stationary): Standard Material Design. Deep menus, configuration, convoy setup allowed.
- **In-Flight** (`IN_VEHICLE` detected): Tactical HUD only. No menus. Two buttons max.

Auto-transition triggered by `ActivityRecognitionClient` detecting `IN_VEHICLE`.

## Tactical OLED Color Palette -- NO Material You In-Flight

```kotlin
// Hardcoded tactical tokens -- NEVER use dynamic Material You colors in-flight
object SlickColors {
    val Void = Color(0xFF000000)       // True OLED black -- pixels physically off
    val Alert = Color(0xFFFF5722)      // Deep orange -- hazards, SOS, tap targets
    val Wash = Color(0xFF00E5FF)       // Cyan -- rain gradient, wind vectors
    val DataPrimary = Color(0xFFFFFFFF) // Pure white -- speed, ETA, distance
    val DataSecondary = Color(0xFF9E9E9E) // Grey -- labels, secondary info
    val Surface = Color(0xFF121212)    // Near-black surface for cards
}
```

Override Material 3 color scheme completely for in-flight screens. Never allow `DynamicColorScheme`.

## Cognitive Zoning (In-Flight Layout)

```
┌─────────────────────────────────┐
│  ZONE 1 (top 20%)               │
│  ← 450 m    110 km/h   14:30   │  ← Peripheral Header
├─────────────────────────────────┤
│                                 │
│  ZONE 2 (middle 50%)            │
│  [MapLibre + GripMatrix polyline]│  ← Tactical Focus
│  Anchored below center          │
│  (shows more route ahead)       │
├─────────────────────────────────┤
│  ZONE 3 (bottom 30%)            │
│  [MARK HAZARD]  [AUDIO MUTE]   │  ← Interaction Deck
└─────────────────────────────────┘
```

Zone 2 map anchor: rider icon at ~55% from top (not center) to maximize forward visibility.

## Typography -- Monospace for All Telemetry Numbers

```kotlin
// ❌ BAD -- SansSerif '1' is narrower than '8', causes jitter at speed
Text("110 km/h", style = MaterialTheme.typography.displayLarge)

// ✅ GOOD -- Monospace prevents horizontal layout shift during speed changes
Text(
    text = "${speedKmh.toInt()} km/h",
    style = TextStyle(
        fontFamily = FontFamily.Monospace,
        fontSize = 32.sp,
        fontWeight = FontWeight.Bold,
        color = SlickColors.DataPrimary,
    )
)
```

**Size rules:**
- Zone 1 telemetry (speed, ETA, distance): 24–32sp Monospace
- Zone 3 button labels: 18–20sp Bold SansSerif
- All HUD text minimum: 14sp -- no exceptions

## Glove-Friendly Interaction

```kotlin
// Zone 3 buttons must fill 50% width each, minimum 60dp height
Row(modifier = Modifier.fillMaxWidth().padding(8.dp)) {
    SlickButton(
        text = "MARK HAZARD",
        modifier = Modifier.weight(1f).height(64.dp),
        color = SlickColors.Alert,
        onClick = onMarkHazard,
    )
    Spacer(modifier = Modifier.width(8.dp))
    SlickButton(
        text = "AUDIO MUTE",
        modifier = Modifier.weight(1f).height(64.dp),
        color = SlickColors.Surface,
        onClick = onToggleMute,
    )
}
```

Long-press for secondary actions. Never require precise taps on small targets while in-flight.

## Direct Sun Mode (Lux Sensor Auto-Inversion)

When `Sensor.TYPE_LIGHT` returns max lux (hardware saturation), hard-invert theme:

```kotlin
val directSunColors = lightColorScheme(
    background = Color.White,
    onBackground = Color.Black,
    primary = Color(0xFFD84315), // Dark orange on white
    surface = Color(0xFFF5F5F5),
    onSurface = Color.Black,
)
```

This overrides the OLED dark theme. The rider's eyes need contrast, not battery savings.

## Democratic Detour Overlay (In-Flight Modal)

```kotlin
// Modal slides up from bottom, blurs map slightly, massive YES/NO targets
Box(modifier = Modifier.fillMaxSize()) {
    // Map beneath (slightly dimmed)
    // Overlay: 50% height bottom sheet
    // Two massive buttons: YES (green) / NO (dark grey)
    // Auto-dismisses after voteExpiry countdown
    // Weather warning text if detour creates hazard
}
```

## Survival Mode UI (Battery < 15%)

Map is killed. Composable replaces Zones 1+2+3 with full-screen text-only:

```kotlin
// Survival HUD -- entire screen, no map
Column(
    modifier = Modifier.fillMaxSize().background(Color.Black),
    horizontalAlignment = Alignment.CenterHorizontally,
) {
    TurnArrow(direction = nextTurn, modifier = Modifier.size(120.dp))  // Massive arrow
    Text("${distanceToTurn} m", fontSize = 48.sp, fontFamily = FontFamily.Monospace)
    Text("${speedKmh.toInt()} km/h", fontSize = 40.sp, fontFamily = FontFamily.Monospace)
    BatteryGauge(level = batteryPercent)  // Critical visual
}
```
